description:
Dictating the Course part 2

The search for Lenny begins as Sam, Alex and their friend from Earth, Mark set off to find the missing djinn. Along the way, they pick up a new comrade-in-arms and begin to unravel the mystery of what the Draxash are up to.
name: Dictating the Course Part Two

description: After foiling a jewelry store heist, professional wrestler The Hangman may be Gotham's newest hero. But Batman knows there's a dark secret behind The Hangman's mask and he's determined to uncover it.
name: The Hangman of Terror Chapter 2 of 4

description:
On no! Minecraft has invaded Beanotown... but Dennis and Gnasher have just the thing to deal with zombie creepers!

Also in Beanotown this week...

  • Minnie goes ape with her new pal!
  • Learn how to put some flour power in your pranking!
  • Transfomers to be won!

PLUS... find out more about our brilliant new app! The Dennis and Gnasher Prank Sticker app is available from the Apple store!

Oh no! Walter has Dennis clapped in handcuffs! Has he finally got the better of the Menace?

Also in Beanotown this week...

  • Make your own gross doggie drool just like Gnasher's!
  • Meet the Trash Street Kids!
  • Will Minnie's Dad survive a Minx-style dance-off?

PLUS... find out more about our brilliant new app! The Dennis and Gnasher Prank Sticker app is available from the Apple store!

It's nearly Christmas in Beanotown, so are the Menace Squad being good? Not a chance!

  • Look out, Softies! Menacing just got mobile!
  • What's hidden behind the doors of Minnie's Dad's advenbt calendar? Two Minxes?!
  • Why's Billy gone to school in his undies?!
  • An unexpected visit from Santa makes it a Merry Whiff-mas with Wallace & Gromit!

PLUS... make a cool Jedi floating cup trick, solve Alexander Lemming's plummet of peril and win awesome goodies!

Find out more about our brilliant new app! The Dennis and Gnasher Prank Sticker app is available from the Apple store!

It's The Beano's top secret pranking prezzie special! Make 2015 the funniest year ever with this awesome feast of funny!

This Beano Christmas spectacular come with...

  • Exclusive hardback Menace Squad book!
  • Prank Sign!
  • Festive trumpet whoopee cushion!
  • Chrimbo poo-ding!

It's the must-have comic for Christmas!

Quiet Talk

Sometimes just doing nothing can be the most powerful threat.
name: Quiet Talk

description:
Unfolding Mysteries

Yin Jian takes steps toward his destiny as he makes a new friend...and feels a strange kinship with her.
name: Unfolding Mysteries

description: Evil forces have found Zoe at home—and her parents have been taken over by The Darkness! Luckily, the mysterious “exchange students” from school come to save Zoe, and they each sport crystals a lot like Zoe’s diamond! What does this all mean, and who are these arrow-shooting, fireball-throwing girls? Team up with Zoe in the next issue of Crystal Cadets!

The Crystal Cadets are on the search for the Pearl Cadet. They’ve got to get to her before The Darkness converts her! Their search takes them to a skateboarding competition, where the evil Emmy has been convincing all the athletes to cheat—powering the Darkness to attack the Cadets! Will they find the Pearl Cadet in time, or will she save them?

Just a Cup of Coffee a Day

What can you get for the price of just a cup of coffee a day. Our hero, Merce, just found out that he bought himself a vampire hunter.
name: Just A Cup of Coffee A Day

description: While continuing their mission to the secondary cryogenic facility, Javier and the Marine Force Recon Team suffer a catastrophic setback after their first major encounter with a roaming clan of swamp apes. Licking their wounds, they are relieved to discover a village of seemingly friendly humans who are the direct descendants of survivors of the Narbala 5 plague. However, that relief is to be short lived, as a villager discloses some dark secrets, and that swamp apes are not the only threat in the forest.
name: Chapter Three

description: The mysterious island of Tartaruga is sinking and no-one knows why! It's up to the Nekton family to investigate, but with Ant and Fontaine trapped in a quickly flooding cave can Jeffrey save them and help uncover the secrets of the island?

Kishu and the Kitten

An orphan kitten meets a stray dog in Little Tokyo.
name: Kishu and the Kitten

description:
Wide Awake

It's the pulse pounding, exciting final chapter in the amazing mini-series! All the answers are finally revealed and the heroes make a final stand. It's the epic showdown between the Dream Reavers and the Spook King. Humanity and the world will never be the same.
name: Wide Awake

description:
A tale of two heroes. One old hero who is a master of the martial arts past his time, and a new reluctant hero who is not a master of any martial arts, but a staunch disciple of nightmares.

They unite against an eternal enemy of man, and themselves.

Dangerous sinkholes are opening all over Stellar City and it's up to the Hero Cats to save the day! Ace, Midnight, Cassiopeia, Belle, Rocket & Rocco explore an underground world filled with new friends and adventures.

Note: The digital edition (12/17/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
Galahad hitches a ride back to St. Barrington under one condition--a news crew is to follow him and film his every move. This will not end well.

Into the Mouth of the Beast

Pulitzer winner Molly Sloan and her intrepid assistant Timmy Mendez hold the key to something big-a groundplan of the "Central Hive". Like it or not, they've joined forces with Ben Wilcott to thwart world-famous mesmerist and stage performer Mysterion the Magnificent. Their mission: get to Tunis before Mysterion and destroy the Central Hive. But just what is the Central Hive and who is this Ben Wilcott...?
name: Into the Mouth of the Beast

description: Jack leaves behind his East Coast life to follow his new love, Rose, into the Wild West, but arrives to find his pulp fiction legend awaits him. When he is called upon to live up to the heroism the novels have written, Jack discovers the depth of his pulp infamy.

Hell hath no fury like a woman scorned!

Follow the epic tale of Jezebel's rise from reluctant queen to all-powerful sorceress - as she unleashes the gods of the underworld... in her quest for supremacy.

It's the long, cruel days of Summer that teach us about who our best friends really are. Lucas and Billy are inseperable, standing together rain or shine. And best friends have a way of looking out for each other, even when it means getting a little dirty.

"Best Friends" is a dark and heavy twist on a Queen's light ballad to friendship and lasting love, "You're My Best Friend". This is the third story in our digital and print collection, KILLER QUEEN, A COMIC ANTHOLOGY inspired by the discography of Queen. Story by Kenneth Whitfield, with art by David Ryan Lompe; letters by Erica Schultz.

The digital version also features Queen-inspired vignettes from artist CGhirardo, including "I Want Out" and "Seeing One in Many Ways".
name: Best Friends

description: Bobby Whittenheimer traded everything to chase the mystery of Jughead. Love, career, success... all were left behind in his quest to kickstart the world and end the stasis that began in 1945. And now, in the next-to-last issue of this epic tale, the answers are finally within reach. Was it all worth it, or are there more sacrifices ahead?

Tap, tap, tap. A raven outside the Arkham Asylum chamber door? Tapping, tapping, tapping. “But I killed the Batman! Are you just in my head?” trembled “Edgar” as the shadowy figure whispered in reply, “Nevermore…”
name: Nevermore..., Part 3 of 3

description:
Righting Wrongs

Whoa! Last issue both Lloyd and Bear had split off and BOTH ended up in trouble!

What they gonna do now? What you gonna do now? Well, why not check out the continuing adventures of Lloyd and Bear?

(And hey, I say 'continuing adventures' but who knows if that's even the case if they don't manage to get out of the trouble they're in!)
name: Righting Wrongs

description: We all know that Lucky Luke has a busy life. When it’s not Washington calling upon him for some national project, it’s the local penitentiary asking him to recapture the Daltons. But not every moment is spent in such grand adventures. Here is a collection of smaller stories depicting the everyday life of our cowboy, from taking a child to the dentist to helping passing settlers – and even attending a classical concert in Houston! What a full life he leads!
name: Seven Stories

description: As the sisters battle The Dragon-Mage to their last breath, darkness stirs in other corners of the valley. Wounded strangers disappear, military forces gather to march, and the dead swarm towards the East...

Say goodbye to the '80s with one final volume of the decade's breakthroughs and breakouts! Mutant mania launches three new X-teams, plus star turns for Cyclops and Colossus! The first shots are fired in the 'Nam, cyborg Coldblood suits up, and Nth Man and Shadowmasters prove that ninjas are 'in!' The Spellbinders weave miracles, the Wolfpack howls, Speedball bounces, Quasar shines, and Wonder Man hogs the spotlight - but it's hell on Earth when Mephisto arrives. Good thing Damage Control is here to clean up! Collecting THE 'NAM #1, COMET MAN #1, FALLEN ANGELS #1, MEPHISTO VS. #1, MARVEL GRAPHIC NOVEL #31, SPELLBOUND (1988) #1, EXCALIBUR SPECIAL EDITION, X-TERMINATORS #1, HAVOK & WOLVERINE: MELTDOWN #1, SHADOWMASTERS #1 - plus material from AMAZING SPIDER-MAN ANNUAL #22; MARVEL AGE ANNUAL #4; and MARVEL COMICS PRESENTS (1988) #10, #17, #25-26, #29 and #38.
name: Volume 3

description: In this exciting issue: Will the wardrobe case be closed? Plus: Another much loved movie gets a fishy makeover!

Mutant Pigs Might Fly

In order to save the lives of their infant sons, Pewfell and Tina must overcome a horde of zombies, an army of chaos, a gigantic mutant pig, and the musical stylings of a narcissistic gnome. The stunning conclusion to the "Drain of Chaos" saga.
name: Mutant Pigs Might Fly

description:
Time for a second round of Pride Adventures, as our heroes face new foes and threats and even find some time to hit the bar!

See Wolf and FabMan take on a team of villains who hit a little close to home!

Watch as Muscle Mary assembles an all-female, all-star super-army to repel an all too familiar invasion force!

Listen in on a meeting at Pride HQ Fantabulosa as a NYC detective calls upon the team for help

And just how do Angel, Frost and Muscle Mary unwind after a hard day of heroing?

Fun, drama and the perfect mojito, all in The Pride Adventures#2!
name: Vol. 2

description:
Opening with Thurim's Knights of Christ battle against the Sons of Rus on the frozen wilderness of Lake Peipus, we witness his stunning watery demise before slamming back into action with Requiem and Rebecca in Necropolis.

New characters and plot twists unfurl with devilish detail and black humour, as we finally gain entrance to Black Sabbat's inner sanctum and meet his Ape of Thoth: the channel to Aiwass, Supreme God of the Limbos.

Under enormous pressure to give way to Thurim and join the Brethren, can Requiem stay strong for Rebecca or will he allow Thurim to take over and lead the battle to destroy Dracula?
name: Hellfire Club

description:
SAMI and the Legend of Visper!

Is the legend of Visper TRUE? Sami the Samurai Squirrel believes so.

Join Sami and her loyal friend Bea, the Bumblebee fairy, as they embark on a quest to locate the villainous Visper! This adventure also includes encounters with Ninja Monkeys, Pesky Pirates, and Tim... the TROLL!

Don't miss the 3rd chapter in this exciting NEW AW YEAH COMICS SERIES from cartoonist SCOOT McMahon!
name: SAMI and the Legend of Visper!

description:
When Thousands Slept In Hell

The can't-miss conclusion is here! Hard-luck private detective Avery has been shot at, beaten up, bombed, drugged and nearly buried alive in his pursuit of missing photojournalist Savannah Loy. As the truth behind her disappearance is finally revealed, so is the true face of power in San Hannibal.

Note: The digital edition (12/17/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: When Thousands Slept In Hell

description: The Sentinels return to their destroyed headquarters to retrieve the mysterious CYPRUS unit. And while the government sanctioned group known as O.R.D.E.R. awaits their return, they aren't alone! Who else is searching for the Sentinels? Things are about to get intense very quickly once again.

The Shadow is dead, a victim of a biological weapon... but his soul survives! Believing that their father's ultimate fate rests in the hidden city of Shambala, the twins Chang and Hsu-Tei carry The Shadow's body deep within the Tibetan mountains, only to find themselves hunted by Chinese authorities and the outlaw denizens of a town called Malice. Meanwhile, without their master's guidance, the agents of The Shadow struggle to find their place in a violent, corrupt world. Intent on curing the disease of crime, the unhinged agent Twitch assumes a fearsome identity of his own as The Inoculator... but his brand of vigilante justice draws the attention of a deadly enemy. Will the network of agents survive an assault by The Avenger, a master of disguise as brutal and unrelenting as The Shadow himself? Dynamite Entertainment proudly presents the complete, ground-breaking "Body & Soul" storyline by Andrew Helfer and Kyle Baker, plus two additional stories of The Shadow's past, revealing the secrets that bind his most loyal agents - Margo Lane, Harry Vincent, Burbank, and more - to his never-ending war!

Note: The digital edition (12/17/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Volume Three

description: The hit Sonic Legacy Series returns with a fourth enormous volume! Over the years, the Sonic comics have inspired thousands of stories, four spin-off series, and a library of graphic novel collections. The legacy of the Sonic Series is a long and proud one! Continue your library of the Blue Blur's earliest adventures with this GIGANTIC collection of thrilling adventures and hilarious antics as only Sonic and the Freedom Fighters could provide! It's perfect for long-time fans of the series or those looking to get in on the ground floor! SONIC: LEGACY VOLUME 4 collects Sonic the Hedgehog #55-74 and is loaded with extra material and special features! This time around, Sonic and Tails are on an epic journey around the world to find the vile sorcerer Ixis Naugus and stop his plans for conquering Mobotropolis -- and the world! Featuring all-new cover art from Sonic comic superstar Ben Bates!
name: Book 4

description: From July 1953, "Blue Men of Tara": Alfie Higgins join the Polaris unit on Tara in Alpha Centuri system and discover a race of giant ants and blue caveman.
name: Blue Men of Tara

description:
Colonel Jenny Rocket, formerly of the Omega 3 Orbital Space Station of Mars, narrowly escapes death at the hands of the Overlord's Armada.

Rescued and cared for by a far advanced species, a peaceful, ancient race of highly intelligent, alien beings, Jenny soon discovers a plan to stop the Evil Overlord and his henchmen.

In payment for her life, Jenny joins forces with the alien being, taking on the dangerous mission which lies ahead. Now, she must find the warriors that will aide her in this mission. A mission whose success or failure will determine the very fate of the universe itself!

Her first stop, a heavily jungled world of Moltic, where she currently finds herself at the mercy of one of its more deadly, indigenous inhabitants.

Rick Remender's extraordinary, critically acclaimed X-Force saga is collected across two volumes! Otherworld, interdimensional home of the Captain Britain Corps, has been invaded by a sorcerous army! Meanwhile, Fantomex stands accused of a crime so heinous that the Corps would rather execute him than defend their gates. Can X-Force repel Otherworld's attackers and still save their teammate? And as X-Force falls to its lowest point, the all-new Brotherhood of Evil Mutants strikes! Led by Wolverine's son, Daken, and specifically designed to dismantle X-Force, this new Brotherhood has a secret agenda - but what does Genesis, young clone of Apocalypse, have to do with it? Can X-Force shut down Daken's Brotherhood in time to save the planet? And does a team of hardened killers like X-Force really deserve a happy ending? Collecting UNCANNY X-FORCE (2010) #19.1 and #20-35.
name: Volume 2

description: After 'Vietnam Journal' concluded its initial comic run the series continued as a featured one-page monthly serial in Gallery Magazine and each page ran in FULL COLOR. This is the first time the Hamburger Hill is restored and presented in its original full color format. From acclaimed writer/artist Don Lomax who served during the Vietnam War and put to paper his experiences. Telling the story through the eyes of a fictional character, that of embedded war reporter Scott 'Journal' Neithammer. This is the concluding collected issue of the events that took place during the battle of Hamburger Hill.
Owari no Seraph Ch. 27
Owari no Seraph Ch. 28

Contents

  • Dragon Ball SD Chapter 34
  • One Piece Party Ch. 1
  • Uchiha Sasuke no Sharingan Den Ch. 2

The Kaiju Wars changed the face of the world's landscape, making some areas-called The Blight-inhospitable. Years after the war, 14-year-old Hadashi rarely thinks of the monsters that once nearly destroyed the earth. So what will happen when he actually encounters one?
name: Chapter One
